code: @Override public void close() throws IOException {     try {         IOHelper.closeIterator(it).     } finally {         // we are now closed         closed = true.         next = null.     } }
public boolean hasNext() {     if (next == null) {         next = checkNext().     }     return next != null. }

public T next() {     if (next == null) {         next = checkNext().     }     if (next != null) {         T ep = next.         next = null.         return ep.     }     throw new NoSuchElementException(). }

protected T checkNext() {     while (!closed && it.hasNext()) {         T ep = it.next().         if (ep != null && (filter == null || filter.test(ep))) {             return ep.         }     }     return null. }
